  "name": "Stole of Civility",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>Woven from swaths of rich brocade silk and embroidered with ancient Azlanti script in golden thread, this stole imparts a noble appearance to even the homeliest of individuals when draped over the shoulders.</p>\n<p>While wearing a stole of civility, you receive a +2 item bonus to Diplomacy checks to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.OX4fy22hQgUHDr0q]{Make an Impression} with humans or @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.DCb62iCBrJXy0Ik6]{Make a Request} of humans, and a +2 item bonus to Intimidation checks against humans.</p>\n<p>The stole also grants you full understanding of the Azlanti language.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Activate</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">A</span> envision</p>\n<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per day</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong> you are a human</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> You gain 10 temporary Hit Points, which last for 10 minutes.</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-effects.Item.i0tm2ZHekp7rGGR3]{Effect: Stole of Civility}</p>"
    },
